<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="452" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="23" pageNumber="452">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,367,393]" pageId="23" pageNumber="452">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a combination of two Latin terms: 
<emphasis box="[982,1061,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="452">brunne</emphasis>
(brown) and 
<emphasis box="[1213,1261,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="452">pedi</emphasis>
(foot), in reference to the dark brown hind tarsomere 1 of males and females of this new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
