<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="452" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="23" pageNumber="452">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,654,680]" pageId="23" pageNumber="452">Discussion.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Grogan, 2020" authorityName="Grogan" authorityYear="2020" box="[444,567,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="452" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="folkertsi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[444,461,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="452">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[475,567,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="452">folkertsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[573,633,655,681]" pageId="23" pageNumber="452" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
also have a dark brown hind femur, tibia and hind tarsomere 1, but they differ from males of this new species in lacking mid and hind femoral spines, the gonostylus is elongate with a rounded apex and with a small pointed inner prong in some specimens. Females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grogan" authorityYear="2020" box="[1088,1212,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="452" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="folkertsi">
<emphasis box="[1088,1105,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="452">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1120,1212,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="452">folkertsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from females of this new species in lacking mid and hind femoral spines, hind tarsomere 1 is light brown, and their spermathecae are subequal-size and very small (length 
<quantity box="[610,777,799,825]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.499999999999998" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="452" unit="mm" value="0.08499999999999999" valueMax="0.09" valueMin="0.08">0.08–0.09 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
